34694e55-aa13-42d2-b498-6f41591ad2d4.do_description: To make the output, you have to...1st row bottom square is purple. 2nd row bottom 3 squares green. 3rd row all black. 4th row bottom 2 square blue. 5th row bottom square red.
34694e55-aa13-42d2-b498-6f41591ad2d4.see_description: In the input, you should see...Black fill. Purple fill on fourth square. Second Row 2nd and 3rd square fill green skip one and fill green. 3rd row all black. Fourth row 1st square blue and 3rd square blue. Fifth row 3rd square red.

3e8f099e-bd08-4d1c-b6e1-22aeff73c5d1.do_description: To make the output, you have to...Move every color down to the bottom row. If there are multiple colors fill grid going vertically. Fill going vertically the same color.
3e8f099e-bd08-4d1c-b6e1-22aeff73c5d1.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same 4x4
3e8f099e-bd08-4d1c-b6e1-22aeff73c5d1.see_description: In the input, you should see...4x4 grid with four different colors

423521ea-96bd-4aed-8830-45f45e600254.do_description: To make the output, you have to...move all pixels down. The colors do not change. Simply move all pixels down until they sit on top of each other. There should not be any black pixels between the same color in a column.
423521ea-96bd-4aed-8830-45f45e600254.grid_description: The output grid size...does not change.
423521ea-96bd-4aed-8830-45f45e600254.see_description: In the input, you should see...four different color pixel shapes each in a column.

6bfa977b-6368-49cc-9a71-299622e4b9a8.do_description: To make the output, you have to... think of the grid as a black field and as the colored squares as being objects floating in space. Gravity is suddenly turned on and all of the block fall vertically to the bottom.  That produces the correct output grid.
6bfa977b-6368-49cc-9a71-299622e4b9a8.grid_description: The output grid size... doesn't change from the input.
6bfa977b-6368-49cc-9a71-299622e4b9a8.see_description: In the input, you should see... grids of squares with colored square scattered.

8d79eca7-5a7d-4a1c-98b7-455cacad8791.do_description: To make the output, you have to...move each color block to the bottom, think like the game where you line up blocks to create lines to get point after point.
8d79eca7-5a7d-4a1c-98b7-455cacad8791.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same
8d79eca7-5a7d-4a1c-98b7-455cacad8791.see_description: In the input, you should see...varying colors on a black background

e4c71698-0293-4d7b-b2ad-916c4c3ffbc2.do_description: To make the output, you have to... move the squares downward toward the bottom of the grid. All squares of the same color should rest on top of the other squares of the same color in a column, with the bottom of each column on the bottom row of the grid. The rest of the squares remain black.
e4c71698-0293-4d7b-b2ad-916c4c3ffbc2.grid_description: The output grid size... remains 5 by 5.
e4c71698-0293-4d7b-b2ad-916c4c3ffbc2.see_description: In the input, you should see... a 5 by 5 black grid with various squares of different colors. All squares of one color will be in the same column.
